<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[317,1271,436,1782]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
– The single female from 
<collectingCountry box="[851,910,1675,1696]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Korea</collectingCountry>
deviates from the female 
<typeStatus box="[1161,1245,1675,1696]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
in three features: (1) mandible less broadening distally, 1.6 (and not 1.75) times as broad as long; (2) antenna with 19 antennomeres (the females from 
<collectingCountry box="[774,838,1732,1753]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Russia</collectingCountry>
with 18–21(–23) antennomeres); (3) ground colour of body rusty brown. The single male matches the original description, body 
<quantity box="[1101,1172,1761,1782]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
